									<h2>Salvaging Fossils on the Jurassic Coast</h2>
									<h3>Along a famed stretch of English coastline, amateur and professional collectors alike fill their satchels with fossils before the 200-million-year-old treasures are reclaimed by the waves.</h3>
									<p class="insidepagethumbinfodate">May 26, 2020 | 1,700 words, 11 photos </p>
